observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Management to:
a. Instruct the GSO to keep and maintain Stock Cards for each and every supply to have an adequate monitoring and immediate information of supplies on hand;
b. Require the Accounting Division to keep and maintain Supplies Ledger Cards to record supplies received, issued and the balance both in quantity and amount;
c. Ensure proper coordination between GSO and Accounting Division to have an updated and reconciled balances in their Stock Cards and Supplies Ledger Cards, respectively; and
d. Prepare and submit the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) for Calendar Year 2021, in compliance with Section 121 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I.

Due to the foregoing lapses noted, we highly recommended that the LCE:
a) Direct the Accountant to record all regular procurements of supplies in their respective inventory accounts, record the same as expense when issuance thereof takes place, and maintain the appropriate ledgers;
b) Direct the General Services Officer to religiously maintain the necessary inventory and supplies’ stock cards; and
c) Direct the two offices to religiously reconcile records with the ledgers on a regular basis;

Recommendations:

a. Require the Municipal Treasurer to adhere strictly to the provision that all payment should be made by check directly payable to the suppliers in accordance with Section 40 of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System (MNGAS) for Local Government Units (LGUs) and to deduct taxes due for remittance to BIR pursuant to BIR Revenue Regulations No. 1-87 dated April 2, 1987;
b. Stop granting reimbursement to all Municipal officials and employees;
c. Ensure that the proper procurement process is implemented by the responsible procurement Department Head.

